        "dom_section_identifier": "rch-pic-acute-abdominal-pain-children-2024-section-0006",
        "position": 5,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Repeated examination is useful to identify the persistence or evolution of signs, and evaluate response to treatment Appropriate analgesia should be used and will not mask potentially serious causes of pain Investigations are guided by the most likely cause. Most children do not need investigations Appendicitis in young children may not present with classic symptoms and can present as sepsis or pe",
