        "heading_path": [
          "Abdominal pain - acute",
          "Assessment",
          "Examination"
        ],
        "dom_section_identifier": "rch-pic-acute-abdominal-pain-children-2024-section-0010",
        "position": 9,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Observe the child's movements, gait, position and level of comfort Vital signs, hydration Abdomen Inspect for distension, herniae, bruising Palpate for focal vs generalized tenderness percussion tenderness and, if negative, rebound tenderness* guarding or rigidity* abdominal masses palpable faeces Serial examination of the abdomen is required Examine genitalia eg for testicular torsion Rectal or v",
