        "dom_section_identifier": "rch-pic-acute-abdominal-pain-children-2024-section-0013",
        "position": 12,
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Treatment will be guided by the likely cause Fluid resuscitation may be required (see Intravenous fluids ) Provide adequate analgesia. IV morphine or intranasal fentanyl may be required as initial analgesia in severe pain (see Acute pain management ) Consider fasting, depending on differential diagnosis. Consider enteral or intravenous fluids if assessment or diagnosis is delayed, eg 4 hours if ve",
